    <fullPolicyText>
      <Value><![CDATA[{
  "markup": "<p>We maintain a <strong>“safe harbor” policy</strong> to ensure exempt employees are properly classified and paid in accordance with federal and state wage laws, including the <em>Fair Labor Standards Act (FLSA)</em>.</p>\n<p>Under this policy:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>We do <strong>not make improper deductions</strong> from the salary of employees classified as exempt under the FLSA.</li>\n<li>If an employee believes an improper deduction has been made, they should promptly report it to their HR Business Partner.</li>\n<li>All reported deductions will be <strong>investigated promptly</strong>. If the investigation confirms an improper deduction, the employee will receive <strong>full reimbursement</strong> in a timely manner.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>This policy ensures we maintain compliance with applicable wage laws and protect your exempt status as defined by federal and state regulations. Our goal is to administer pay practices with fairness, accuracy, and transparency.</p>\n<p>If you have questions or concerns about your exempt status or deductions from your pay, please contact the HR team.</p>",
